Gilbert, the most intense hurricane on record, is surging toward Texas after battering the  Yucatan Peninsula.
Gilbert is moving at 15 mph and dumping up to 10 inches of rain.
A  hurricane watch is in effect along the northeastern Mexico coast and the entire Texas  coast.
Gilbert raged through the Caribbean before battering the Yucatan on Wednesday.
Jamaica was the hardest hit with damage estimated at $8 billion.
In Mexico, thousands  were evacuated, with luxury hotels and homes badly damaged, electricity and  communications severed, and flooding widespread.
Gilbert was downgraded to a  Category 3 this morning. 
